Document: CanvasItem
Path: godot/classes/class_canvasitem.rst
Summary: A list of properties for the CanvasItem class, detailing their type and default values for features like visibility, color modulation, materials, and rendering order.

* clip_children (ClipChildrenMode): The clipping mode for children of this CanvasItem. Default: 0.
* light_mask (int): The render layers that 2D lights influence this CanvasItem. Default: 1.
* material (Material): The Material used to draw this item.
* modulate (Color): The color that modulates this CanvasItem and its children. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1).
* self_modulate (Color): The color that modulates this CanvasItem specifically, without affecting its children. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1).
* show_behind_parent (bool): If true, the node is drawn behind its parent. Default: false.
* texture_filter (TextureFilter): The texture filtering mode to be used on this CanvasItem. Default: 0.
* texture_repeat (TextureRepeat): The texture repeating mode to be used on this CanvasItem. Default: 0.
* top_level (bool): If true, this CanvasItem will be drawn on a separate canvas and not inherit its parent's transform. Default: false.
* use_parent_material (bool): If true, the item will use the material of its parent. Default: false.
* visibility_layer (int): The render layer this CanvasItem is part of. It will only be visible if enabled in the Viewport. Default: 1.
* visible (bool): If true, this CanvasItem is drawn. Default: true.
* y_sort_enabled (bool): If true, child nodes are sorted by their Y position. Default: false.
* z_as_relative (bool): If true, the Z index is relative to the parent's Z index. If false, it is absolute. Default: true.
* z_index (int): The Z index, which controls the drawing order. Items with a higher Z index are drawn on top. Default: 0.
